FT  30 JUN 92 / Construction Contracts: Sheltered housing
A sheltered housing development in Leeds features in over Pounds 4.3m worth
of new orders awarded to MOWLEM NORTHERN. The Pounds 1.3m project for Anchor
Housing will provide 35 self-contained flats for retired people and calls
for completion in October.
Having completed three earlier phases, the company has been awarded a fourth
contract for Swedish newsprint manufacturer Stora to construct a rail
transit shed, timber store and handling facilities at Immingham (Pounds 2m).
